    <section id="deployment">
      <title>Designing a deployment</title>
      <p>A Media Encoding Cluster deployment can be as simple as one computer or as complex as multiple clusters of Nodes.</p>
<p>You must run the installer on each computer on which you want to run Media Encoding Cluster. After running the installer, you can configure the system to run as a server or a client.</p>
<p>This Version comes with all dependencies included, no additional Installation or other Programms are needed, i.e. MySql nor ffmpeg needs extra to be installed!</p>
<p>The Installer build a Directory structure like: </p>
        <p class="quote">
        INSTALL_BASE/bin<br/>
        INSTALL_BASE/hive<br/>
        INSTALL_BASE/res<br/>
        INSTALL_BASE/web<br/>
        INSTALL_BASE/tmp<br/>
        </p>
<p>- In the "bin" Directory will be the mhive.exe -> this is the Main Executable to start the Server and the Client.</p>
<p>- In the "hive" Directory will be the MySQL Table to store the Meta Information.</p>
<p>- In the "res" Directory will be the Message Resource Bundle for the different Langauge Packs.</p>
<p>- In the "web" Directory will be the static Resources for Web Administrator.</p>
<p>- In the "tmp" Directory will be the Encoded Chunks that will be used for the Resulting Video.</p>

